AMACO-QP: Enhanced Adaptive Multi-Colony ACO-Based Query Processing

The proposed research introduces AMACO-QP, a groundbreaking healthcare-aware optimization framework that integrates distributed multi-colony Ant Colony Optimization (ACO) with a specialized clinical cost model to achieve scalable and high-integrity query processing for large-scale Electronic Health Record (EHR) datasets. Unlike conventional cost-based optimizers that treat all queries uniformly, this study fuses Apache Spark-based optimization, Hadoop (HDFS) storage, and Presto interactive query execution to incorporate clinical priority, evidence-based credibility scoring, and HIPAA-compliant privacy constraints into the query planning process. By leveraging domain-specific ant colonies—specialized for emergency, research, and routine workflows—and pre-trained clinical NLP for intent recognition, the framework enables sub-second response times for critical queries while achieving a 60% reduction in data scan costs through patient-journey-aware partitioning. This integrated combination of federated multi-objective optimization, healthcare-specific cost modeling, and big data infrastructure represents a first-of-its-kind contribution to the domain of clinical informatics and scalable healthcare analytics.
